1
00:00:00,843 --> 00:00:04,972
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
has introduced his conception

2
00:00:04,972 --> 00:00:09,655
known as ‘the subjective evolution 
of consciousness’.

3
00:00:10,151 --> 00:00:16,540
And part of it is understanding
something he calls

4
00:00:17,372 --> 00:00:20,412
chayabhas or chidabhas.
 

5
00:00:20,412 --> 00:00:23,682
[The Subjective Reality Is the Basis 
of the Objective World]

6
00:00:23,808 --> 00:00:26,709
And it’s like this:

7
00:00:26,709 --> 00:00:29,542
‘cit’ means consciousness.

8
00:00:29,542 --> 00:00:32,984
So we have 
what’s called ‘the cit jagat’.

9
00:00:32,984 --> 00:00:35,835
The spiritual world 
can be described in different ways.

10
00:00:35,855 --> 00:00:37,941
Jagat means ‘world’.

11
00:00:37,941 --> 00:00:40,959
So the cit jagat
means ‘the conscious world’

12
00:00:40,959 --> 00:00:43,768
the world of consciousness.

13
00:00:43,768 --> 00:00:47,265
Then there is the acit jagat,

14
00:00:47,265 --> 00:00:52,697
means the unconscious world,
the objective world.

15
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:56,845
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj’s given 
an excellent example by saying,

16
00:00:56,845 --> 00:01:01,182
“The whole objective world 
is like an iceberg

17
00:01:01,182 --> 00:01:04,633
floating in an ocean 
of consciousness.”

18
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:07,401
Thus we have 
to grasp this idea.

19
00:01:07,451 --> 00:01:10,803
The whole objective world
is like an iceberg

20
00:01:10,803 --> 00:01:14,484
floating in an ocean 
of consciousness.

21
00:01:14,864 --> 00:01:17,872
We know also 
from Jaiva‒Dharma

22
00:01:17,872 --> 00:01:20,410
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur reminding us

23
00:01:20,410 --> 00:01:26,951
that ice is not 
the natural condition of water.

24
00:01:26,954 --> 00:01:30,745
So when it’s 
in that unnatural state

25
00:01:30,746 --> 00:01:34,041
you can say it’s hard,
it’s this …

26
00:01:34,041 --> 00:01:43,976
you can determine, 
observe so many attributes.

27
00:01:43,976 --> 00:01:48,708
But when it resumes
its natural and normal state,

28
00:01:48,718 --> 00:01:53,836
it will be different.

29
00:01:53,836 --> 00:01:59,728
So things like this table 
[knocking]—

30
00:01:59,728 --> 00:02:04,888
this is hard, 
it’s coated in lacquer,

31
00:02:04,888 --> 00:02:14,403
it has depth, height, width,
color, weight.

32
00:02:14,403 --> 00:02:17,854
Those are all concepts:

33
00:02:17,854 --> 00:02:20,839
height, weight, length, 
breadth, dimensions,

34
00:02:20,839 --> 00:02:25,904
depth, color—
these are all concepts.

35
00:02:25,904 --> 00:02:29,697
So Śrīla Guru Mahārāj
is telling us

36
00:02:29,697 --> 00:02:34,705
that an object is a cluster 
of subjective concepts

37
00:02:34,705 --> 00:02:36,285
that’s what an object is—

38
00:02:36,285 --> 00:02:40,831
it’s a cluster 
of subjective concepts.

39
00:02:40,891 --> 00:02:43,416
And so that’s 
what one object is

40
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,968
that’s what
the whole objective world is.

41
00:02:45,968 --> 00:02:50,831
It’s like an iceberg 
floating in an ocean of consciousness.

42
00:02:51,319 --> 00:02:54,805
He’ll make reference to Berkeley,

43
00:02:54,805 --> 00:03:00,179
Bishop Berkeley 
and his theory

44
00:03:01,499 --> 00:03:05,471
which is represented
in a slogan that

45
00:03:05,471 --> 00:03:09,359
“The world is in the mind.”

46
00:03:10,509 --> 00:03:14,529
Now this is easily parodied.
People will say,

47
00:03:14,529 --> 00:03:22,742
“Oh, I see, you mean like
all of this is just in my mind, right?”

48
00:03:22,742 --> 00:03:25,635
That’s not what 
he is saying.

49
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,490
And as Woody Allen 
once joked.

50
00:03:29,490 --> 00:03:35,007
He said, “If everything …
if world is in the mind,

51
00:03:35,007 --> 00:03:40,844
then that car I bought last week
was really overpriced.”

52
00:03:40,844 --> 00:03:42,780
[Laughing]

53
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:46,350
But that’s not 
what he means

54
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:48,620
when he says 
the world is in the mind.

55
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:49,959
He means to say

56
00:03:49,959 --> 00:03:54,851
this whole objective world,
all of these objects

57
00:03:54,861 --> 00:03:58,317
are floating 
in an ocean of consciousness.

58
00:03:58,317 --> 00:04:00,953
Consciousness is the basis.

59
00:04:00,953 --> 00:04:05,069
The subjective reality 
is the basis of the objective world.

60
00:04:05,069 --> 00:04:08,630
That’s what he means to say.
Not that it doesn’t exist,

61
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:12,817
but he is tracing the source 
of its existence to consciousness.

62
00:04:12,817 --> 00:04:15,476
Consciousness being
the primordial substance.

